{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'll just take you to Bangladesh for a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"Before I tell that story, we should ask ourselves the question:"},{"time":45000,"text":"Why does poverty exist?"},{"time":47000,"text":"I mean, there is plenty of knowledge and scientific breakthroughs."},{"time":52000,"text":"We all live in the same planet,"},{"time":55000,"text":"but there's still a great deal of poverty in the world."},{"time":57000,"text":"And I think -- so I want to throw a perspective that I have,"},{"time":61000,"text":"so that we can assess this project, or any other project, for that matter,"},{"time":68000,"text":"to see whether it's contributing or --"},{"time":71000,"text":"contributing to poverty or trying to alleviate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73000,"text":"Rich countries have been sending aid to poor countries for the last 60 years."},{"time":78000,"text":"And by and large, this has failed."},{"time":81000,"text":"And you can see this book,"},{"time":83000,"text":"written by someone who worked in the World Bank for 20 years,"},{"time":86000,"text":"and he finds economic growth in this country to be elusive."},{"time":91000,"text":"By and large, it did not work."},{"time":94000,"text":"So the question is, why is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"In my mind, there is something to learn from the history of Europe."},{"time":103000,"text":"I mean, even here, yesterday I was walking across the street,"},{"time":107000,"text":"and they showed three bishops were executed 500 years ago,"},{"time":111000,"text":"right across the street from here."},{"time":113000,"text":"So my point is, there's a lot of struggle has gone in Europe,"},{"time":117000,"text":"where citizens were empowered by technologies."},{"time":120000,"text":"And they demanded authorities from --"},{"time":123000,"text":"to come down from their high horses."},{"time":126000,"text":"And in the end, there's better bargaining"},{"time":129000,"text":"between the authorities and citizens,"},{"time":132000,"text":"and democracies, capitalism -- everything else flourished."},{"time":135000,"text":"And so you can see, the real process of --"},{"time":138000,"text":"and this is backed up by this 500-page book --"},{"time":142000,"text":"that the authorities came down and citizens got up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"But if you look, if you have that perspective,"},{"time":150000,"text":"then you can see what happened in the last 60 years."},{"time":153000,"text":"Aid actually did the opposite."},{"time":156000,"text":"It empowered authorities,"},{"time":158000,"text":"and, as a result, marginalized citizens."},{"time":161000,"text":"The authorities did not have the reason to make economic growth happen"},{"time":164000,"text":"so that they could tax people"},{"time":167000,"text":"and make more money for to run their business."},{"time":171000,"text":"Because they were getting it from abroad."},{"time":174000,"text":"And in fact, if you see oil-rich countries,"},{"time":178000,"text":"where citizens are not yet empowered, the same thing goes --"},{"time":181000,"text":"Nigeria, Saudi Arabia, all sorts of countries."},{"time":184000,"text":"Because the aid and oil or mineral money acts the same way."},{"time":189000,"text":"It empowers authorities, without activating the citizens --"},{"time":193000,"text":"their hands, legs, brains, what have you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"And if you agree with that, then I think the best way to improve these countries"},{"time":203000,"text":"is to recognize that economic development is of the people,"},{"time":206000,"text":"by the people, for the people."},{"time":209000,"text":"And that is the real network effect."},{"time":211000,"text":"If citizens can network and make themselves more organized and productive,"},{"time":215000,"text":"so that their voices are heard,"},{"time":217000,"text":"so then things would improve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"And to contrast that, you can see the most important institution in the world,"},{"time":224000,"text":"the World Bank, is an organization of the government,"},{"time":228000,"text":"by the government, for the governments."},{"time":231000,"text":"Just see the contrast."},{"time":233000,"text":"And that is the perspective I have, and then I can start my story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"Of course, how would you empower citizens?"},{"time":241000,"text":"There could be all sorts of technologies. And one is cell phones."},{"time":243000,"text":"Recently \"The Economist\" recognized this,"},{"time":246000,"text":"but I stumbled upon the idea 12 years ago,"},{"time":251000,"text":"and that's what I've been working on."},{"time":257000,"text":"So 12 years ago, I was trying to be an investment banker in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"We had -- quite a few our colleagues were connected by a computer network."},{"time":268000,"text":"And we got more productive because we didn't have to exchange floppy disks;"},{"time":275000,"text":"we could update each other more often."},{"time":279000,"text":"But one time it broke down."},{"time":281000,"text":"And it reminded me of a day in 1971."},{"time":285000,"text":"There was a war going on in my country."},{"time":289000,"text":"And my family moved out of an urban place, where we used to live,"},{"time":292000,"text":"to a remote rural area where it was safer."},{"time":296000,"text":"And one time my mother asked me to get some medicine for a younger sibling."},{"time":299000,"text":"And I walked 10 miles or so, all morning, to get there, to the medicine man."},{"time":306000,"text":"And he wasn't there, so I walked all afternoon back."},{"time":309000,"text":"So I had another unproductive day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"So while I was sitting in a tall building in New York,"},{"time":314000,"text":"I put those two experiences together side by side,"},{"time":317000,"text":"and basically concluded that connectivity is productivity --"},{"time":320000,"text":"whether it's in a modern office or an underdeveloped village."},{"time":325000,"text":"So naturally, I -- the implication of that is"},{"time":328000,"text":"that the telephone is a weapon against poverty."},{"time":333000,"text":"And if that's the case, then the question is"},{"time":335000,"text":"how many telephones did we have at that time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"And it turns out, that there was one telephone in Bangladesh"},{"time":344000,"text":"for every 500 people."},{"time":346000,"text":"And all those phones were in the few urban places."},{"time":350000,"text":"The vast rural areas, where 100 million people lived,"},{"time":353000,"text":"there were no telephones."},{"time":356000,"text":"So just imagine how many man-months or man-years are wasted,"},{"time":359000,"text":"just like I wasted a day."},{"time":362000,"text":"If you just multiply by 100 million people, let's say losing one day a month,"},{"time":366000,"text":"whatever, and you see a vast amount of resource wasted."},{"time":370000,"text":"And after all, poor countries, like rich countries, one thing we've got equal,"},{"time":373000,"text":"is their days are the same length: 24 hours."},{"time":376000,"text":"So if you lose that precious resource,"},{"time":379000,"text":"where you are somewhat equal to the richer countries,"},{"time":382000,"text":"that's a huge waste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"So I started looking for any evidence that --"},{"time":389000,"text":"does connectivity really increase productivity?"},{"time":393000,"text":"And I couldn't find much, really, but I found this graph produced by the ITU,"},{"time":397000,"text":"which is the International Telecommunication Union, based in Geneva."},{"time":403000,"text":"They show an interesting thing."},{"time":406000,"text":"That you see, the horizontal axis is where you place your country."},{"time":410000,"text":"So the United States or the UK would be here, outside."},{"time":413000,"text":"And so the impact of one new telephone,"},{"time":417000,"text":"which is on the vertical axis, is very little."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422000,"text":"But if you come back to a poorer country, where the GNP per capita is,"},{"time":425000,"text":"let's say, 500 dollars, or 300 dollars,"},{"time":428000,"text":"then the impact is huge: 6,000 dollars. Or 5,000 dollars."},{"time":435000,"text":"The question was,"},{"time":436000,"text":"how much did it cost to install a new telephone in Bangladesh?"},{"time":440000,"text":"It turns out: 2,000 dollars."},{"time":444000,"text":"So if you spend 2,000 dollars, and let's say the telephone lasts 10 years,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and if 5,000 dollars every year -- so that's 50,000 dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"So obviously this was a gadget to have."},{"time":454000,"text":"And of course, if the cost of installing a telephone is going down,"},{"time":459000,"text":"because there's a digital revolution going on,"},{"time":461000,"text":"then it would be even more dramatic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"And I knew a little economics by then --"},{"time":468000,"text":"it says Adam Smith taught us that specialization leads to productivity."},{"time":471000,"text":"But how would you specialize?"},{"time":474000,"text":"Let's say I'm a fisherman and a farmer."},{"time":478000,"text":"And Chris is a fisherman farmer. Both are generalists."},{"time":484000,"text":"So the point is that we could only -- the only way we could depend on each other,"},{"time":488000,"text":"is if we can connect with each other."},{"time":491000,"text":"And if we are neighbors, I could just walk over to his house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"But then we are limiting our economic sphere to something very small area."},{"time":500000,"text":"But in order to expand that, you need a river,"},{"time":503000,"text":"or you need a highway, or you need telephone lines."},{"time":505000,"text":"But in any event, it's connectivity that leads to dependability."},{"time":510000,"text":"And that leads to specialization."},{"time":512000,"text":"That leads to productivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"So the question was, I started looking at this issue,"},{"time":518000,"text":"and going back and forth between Bangladesh and New York."},{"time":520000,"text":"There were a lot of reasons people told me"},{"time":524000,"text":"why we don't have enough telephones."},{"time":527000,"text":"And one of them is the lacking buying power."},{"time":529000,"text":"Poor people apparently don't have the power to buy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"But the point is, if it's a production tool, why do we have to worry about that?"},{"time":535000,"text":"I mean, in America, people buy cars,"},{"time":538000,"text":"and they put very little money down."},{"time":541000,"text":"They get a car, and they go to work."},{"time":544000,"text":"The work pays them a salary;"},{"time":547000,"text":"the salary allows them to pay for the car over time."},{"time":550000,"text":"The car pays for itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551000,"text":"So if the telephone is a production tool,"},{"time":554000,"text":"then we don't quite have to worry about the purchasing power."},{"time":557000,"text":"And of course, even if that's true, then what about initial buying power?"},{"time":562000,"text":"So then the question is, why can't we have some kind of shared access?"},{"time":567000,"text":"In the United States, we have -- everybody needs a banking service,"},{"time":571000,"text":"but very few of us are trying to buy a bank."},{"time":574000,"text":"So it's -- a bank tends to serve a whole community."},{"time":578000,"text":"So we could do that for telephones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"And also people told me that we have a lot of important primary needs to meet:"},{"time":586000,"text":"food, clothing, shelter, whatever."},{"time":589000,"text":"But again, it's very paternalistic."},{"time":591000,"text":"You should be raising income"},{"time":594000,"text":"and let people decide what they want to do with their money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599000,"text":"But the real problem is the lack of other infrastructures."},{"time":602000,"text":"See, you need some kind of infrastructure to bring a new thing."},{"time":607000,"text":"For instance, the Internet was booming in the U.S."},{"time":610000,"text":"because there were -- there were people who had computers."},{"time":613000,"text":"They had modems."},{"time":615000,"text":"They had telephone lines, so it's very easy to bring in a new idea, like the Internet."},{"time":619000,"text":"But that's what's lacking in a poor country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"So for example, we didn't have ways to have credit checks,"},{"time":624000,"text":"few banks to collect bills, etc."},{"time":629000,"text":"But that's why I noticed Grameen Bank, which is a bank for poor people,"},{"time":632000,"text":"and had 1,100 branches, 12,000 employees, 2.3 million borrowers."},{"time":639000,"text":"And they had these branches."},{"time":641000,"text":"I thought I could put cell towers and create a network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"And anyway, to cut the time short -- so I started --"},{"time":650000,"text":"I first went to them and said,"},{"time":653000,"text":"\"You know, perhaps I could connect all your branches and make you more efficient.\""},{"time":656000,"text":"But you know, they have, after all, evolved in a country without telephones,"},{"time":660000,"text":"so they are decentralized. I mean, of course there might be other good reasons,"},{"time":665000,"text":"but this was one of the reasons -- they had to be."},{"time":667000,"text":"And so they were not that interested to connect all their branches,"},{"time":671000,"text":"and then to be -- and rock the boat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"So I started focusing. What is it that they really do?"},{"time":677000,"text":"So what happens is that somebody borrows money from the bank."},{"time":680000,"text":"She typically buys a cow. The cow gives milk."},{"time":684000,"text":"And she sells the milk to the villagers, and pays off the loan."},{"time":688000,"text":"And this is a business for her, but it's milk for everybody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"And suddenly I realized that a cell phone could be a cow."},{"time":695000,"text":"Because some way she could borrow 200 dollars from the bank,"},{"time":699000,"text":"get a phone and have the phone for everybody."},{"time":702000,"text":"And it's a business for her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"So I wrote to the bank, and they thought for a while, and they said,"},{"time":709000,"text":"\"It's a little crazy, but logical."},{"time":711000,"text":"If you think it can be done, come and make it happen.\""},{"time":715000,"text":"So I quit my job; I went back to Bangladesh."},{"time":718000,"text":"I created a company in America called Gonofone,"},{"time":721000,"text":"which in Bengali means \"people's phone.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":724000,"text":"And angel investors in America put in money into that."},{"time":726000,"text":"I flew around the world."},{"time":728000,"text":"After about a million -- I mean, I got rejected from lots of places,"},{"time":731000,"text":"because I was not only trying to go to a poor country,"},{"time":734000,"text":"I was trying to go to the poor of the poor country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"After about a million miles, and a meaningful --"},{"time":740000,"text":"a substantial loss of hair, I eventually put together a consortium, and --"},{"time":743000,"text":"which involved the Norwegian telephone company,"},{"time":747000,"text":"which provided the know-how,"},{"time":750000,"text":"and the Grameen Bank provided the infrastructure to spread the service."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"To make the story short, here is the coverage of the country."},{"time":760000,"text":"You can see it's pretty much covered."},{"time":763000,"text":"Even in Bangladesh, there are some empty places."},{"time":766000,"text":"But we are also investing around another 300 million dollars this year"},{"time":770000,"text":"to extend that coverage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"Now, about that cow model I talked about."},{"time":778000,"text":"There are about 115,000 people who are retailing telephone services"},{"time":784000,"text":"in their neighborhoods."},{"time":786000,"text":"And it's serving 52,000 villages, which represent about 80 million people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"And these phones are generating"},{"time":796000,"text":"about 100 million dollars for the company."},{"time":799000,"text":"And two dollars profit per entrepreneur per day, which is like 700 dollars per year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808000,"text":"And of course, it's very beneficial in a lot of ways."},{"time":810000,"text":"It increases income, improves welfare, etc."},{"time":813000,"text":"And the result is, right now, this company is the largest telephone company,"},{"time":817000,"text":"with 3.5 million subscribers,"},{"time":820000,"text":"115,000 of these phones I talked about --"},{"time":822000,"text":"that produces about a third of the traffic in the network."},{"time":827000,"text":"And 2004, the net profit, after taxes --"},{"time":831000,"text":"very serious taxes -- was 120 million dollars."},{"time":835000,"text":"And the company contributed about 190 million dollars to the government coffers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"And again, here are some of the lessons."},{"time":843000,"text":"\"The government needs to provide economically viable services.\""},{"time":845000,"text":"Actually, this is an instance where private companies can provide that."},{"time":848000,"text":"\"Governments need to subsidize private companies.\""},{"time":851000,"text":"This is what some people think."},{"time":853000,"text":"And actually, private companies help governments with taxes."},{"time":856000,"text":"\"Poor people are recipients.\""},{"time":858000,"text":"Poor people are a resource."},{"time":861000,"text":"\"Services cost too much for the poor.\""},{"time":863000,"text":"Their involvement reduces the cost."},{"time":867000,"text":"\"The poor are uneducated and cannot do much.\""},{"time":870000,"text":"They are very eager learners and very capable survivors."},{"time":873000,"text":"I've been very surprised."},{"time":875000,"text":"Most of them learn how to operate a telephone within a day."},{"time":878000,"text":"\"Poor countries need aid.\""},{"time":881000,"text":"Businesses -- this one company has raised the --"},{"time":884000,"text":"if the ideal figures are even five percent true, this one company"},{"time":889000,"text":"is raising the GNP of the country much more than the aid the country receives."},{"time":894000,"text":"And as I was trying to show you, as far as I'm concerned,"},{"time":897000,"text":"aid does damages because it removes the government from its citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"And this is a new project I have with Dean Kamen, the famous inventor in America."},{"time":906000,"text":"He has produced some power generators,"},{"time":909000,"text":"which we are now doing an experiment in Bangladesh,"},{"time":913000,"text":"in two villages where cow manure is producing biogas,"},{"time":916000,"text":"which is running these generators."},{"time":920000,"text":"And each of these generators is selling electricity to 20 houses each."},{"time":923000,"text":"It's just an experiment."},{"time":927000,"text":"We don't know how far it will go,"},{"time":928000,"text":"but it's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}